body:
iverilog expects the address of an array to be 2 bits larger than it should be. This can be observed well when converting the following code  to verilog95 using iverilog:

```verilog
module test(input [4:0] addr, output out);
    reg memory [31:0]
    assign out = memory[addr];
endmodule

```
becomes
```verilog
module test(addr, out);
    input [4:0] addr;
    reg memory [31:0];
    wire out;

   assign out = memory[{2'h0, addr} + 0]
endmodule
```

